ne Raymond]], American actor (d. [[1998]])\n* [[August 18]] &ndash; [[Edgar Faure]], 2-time [[Prime Minister of France]] (d. [[1988]])\n* [[August 21]]\n** [[M. M. Kaye]], British writer (d. [[2004]])\n** [[Tom Tully]], American actor (d. [[1982]])\n* [[August 22]] &ndash; [[Henri Cartier-Bresson]], French photographer (d. [[2004]])\n* [[August 27]]\n** [[Donald Bradman]], Australian cricketer (d. [[2001]])\n** [[Lyndon B. Johnson]], 36th [[President of the United States]] (d. [[1973]])\n* [[August 28]] &ndash; [[Robert Merle]], French writer (d. [[2004]])\n* [[August 30]]\n** [[Leonor Fini]], Argentine artist (d. [[1996]])\n** [[Fred MacMurray]], American actor (d. [[1991]])\n* [[August 31]] &ndash; [[William Saroyan]], American writer (d. [[1981]])\n\n=== September===\n[[File:Richard Wright.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Richard Wright (author)|Richard Wright]]]]\n<!--[[File:Balafrej2wiki.png|thumb|100px|[[Ahmed Balafrej]]]]-->\n[[File:PennySingleton.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Penny Singleton]]]]\n[[File:Eddie Tolan 1932.jpg|thumb|100px|[[Eddie Tolan]]]]\n* [[September 2]] \n** [[Ruth Bancroft]], American landscape, garden designer (d. [[2017]])\n** [[Nikolai Aleksandrovich Kozyrev]],  Russian astronomer, astrophysicist (d. [[1983]])\n** [[Dorothea Leighton]], American social psychiatrist, founded the field of medical anthropology (d. [[1989]])\n* [[September 3]] &ndash; [[Lev Pontryagin]], Russian mathematician (d. [[1988]])\n* [[September 4]] &ndash; [[Richard Wright (author)|Richard Wright]], African-American author (d. [[1960]])\n* [[September 5]]\n** [[Ahmed Balafrej]], Moroccan politician, Foreign Minister and 2nd [[Prime Minister of Morocco]] (d. [[1990]])\n** [[Josu\u00e9 de Castro]], Brazilian activist against hunger (d. [[1973]])\n** [[Cecilia Seghizzi]], Italian composer, painter (d. [[2019]])\n* [[September 6]]\n** [[Louis Essen]], English physicist (d. [[1997]])\n** [[Anthony Wagner]], British herald at the College of Arms (d. [[1995]])\n* [[September 7]] &ndash; [[Michael