{"title_page": "Wayne Cooney", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=December 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name              = Wayne Cooney\n| image             = \n| caption           =\n| fullname          = \n| birth_date        = {{birth date and age|1968|3|23|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Birmingham]], England\n| position          = [[Full back (association football)|Full back]]\n| youthyears1       = {{0|000}}?\u20131988 | youthclubs1 = [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]]\n| years1 = 1988\u20131992  |  clubs1 = [[Shamrock Rovers F.C.|Shamrock Rovers]]             | caps1 = | goals1 = \n| years2 = 1992\u20131994  |  clubs2 = [[Dundalk F.C.|Dundalk]]                             | caps2 = | goals2 =\n| years3 = 1994\u20131995  |  clubs3 = [[Bohemian F.C.|Bohemians]]                           | caps3 = | goals3 =\n| nationalyears1 = 1984\u20131986\n| nationalteam1 = [[Republic of Ireland national under-19 football team|Republic of Ireland U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = ?\n| nationalgoals1 = ?\n}}\n'''Wayne Cooney''' (born 23 March 1968) is a former [[association football|footballer]] who played in the [[League of Ireland]] during the 1990s.\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Birmingham]], Cooney started his career at [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] before returning to Dublin to sign for [[Noel King]]'s [[Shamrock Rovers]] side in 1988. He made his debut on 4 September <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/archive/1988/0905/Pg002.html#Ar00206:5A550967256749A5A84D95C24E35EB50F6004946364C064B4C36904EF6A65ED5F661960B54164057165853F74656D75C63967D66969467F6F66AF70643C5A84985C249A5EA4DB5FF6356F6678706 |title=Archived copy |access-date=17 July 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110221060628/http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/archive/1988/0905/Pg002.html#Ar00206:5A550967256749A5A84D95C24E35EB50F6004946364C064B4C36904EF6A65ED5F661960B54164057165853F74656D75C63967D66969467F6F66AF70643C5A84985C249A5EA4DB5FF6356F6678706 |archive-date=21 February 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and became a popular figure with the fans in his 4 years at Rovers. He made a total of 127 appearances scoring 6 times for the Hoops.\n\nHe then moved to [[Dundalk FC|Dundalk]]. After a couple of seasons at [[Oriel Park]], he became [[Turlough O'Connor (footballer)|Turlough O'Connor]]'s first signing for [[Bohemian FC|Bohemians]] where he scored his debut for Bohs on 3 January 1994 in a 2-0 league win over [[Cobh Ramblers]].<ref>Bohemian FC match programme, Vol. 46, no. 5</ref> He made 4 appearances in European competition for Bohs, all of them in the 1995 [[Intertoto Cup]].\n\nCooney earned caps for the [[Republic of Ireland national under-19 football team|Republic of Ireland national under-19 team]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cooney, Wayne}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland association footballers]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n[[Category:Shamrock Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bohemian F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Dundalk F.C. players]]\n[[Category:League of Ireland players]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:English people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Birmingham, West Midlands]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=December 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name              = Wayne Cooney\n| image             = \n| caption           =\n| fullname          = \n| birth_date        = {{birth date and age|1968|3|23|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Birmingham]], England\n| position          = [[Full back (association football)|Full back]]\n| youthyears1       = {{0|000}}?\u20131988 | youthclubs1 = [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]]\n| years1 = 1988\u20131992  |  clubs1 = [[Shamrock Rovers F.C.|Shamrock Rovers]]             | caps1 = ? | goals1 = ?\n| years2 = 1992\u20131994  |  clubs2 = [[Dundalk F.C.|Dundalk]]                             | caps2 = ? | goals2 = ?\n| years3 = 1994\u20131995  |  clubs3 = [[Bohemian F.C.|Bohemian]]                           | caps3 = ? | goals3 = ?\n| nationalyears1 = 1984\u20131986\n| nationalteam1 = [[Republic of Ireland national under-19 football team|Republic of Ireland U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = ?\n| nationalgoals1 = ?\n}}\n'''Wayne Cooney''' (born 23 March 1968) is a former [[association football]] player who played in the [[League of Ireland]] during the 1990s.\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Birmingham]], Cooney started his career at [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] before returning to Dublin to sign for [[Noel King]]'s [[Shamrock Rovers]] side in 1988. He made his debut on 4 September <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/archive/1988/0905/Pg002.html#Ar00206:5A550967256749A5A84D95C24E35EB50F6004946364C064B4C36904EF6A65ED5F661960B54164057165853F74656D75C63967D66969467F6F66AF70643C5A84985C249A5EA4DB5FF6356F6678706 |title=Archived copy |access-date=17 July 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110221060628/http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/archive/1988/0905/Pg002.html#Ar00206:5A550967256749A5A84D95C24E35EB50F6004946364C064B4C36904EF6A65ED5F661960B54164057165853F74656D75C63967D66969467F6F66AF70643C5A84985C249A5EA4DB5FF6356F6678706 |archive-date=21 February 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and became a popular figure with the fans in his 4 years at Rovers. He made a total of 127 appearances scoring 6 times for the Hoops.\n\nHe then moved to [[Dundalk FC|Dundalk]]. After a couple of seasons at [[Oriel Park]], he became [[Turlough O'Connor (footballer)|Turlough O'Connor]]'s first signing for [[Bohemian FC|Bohemians]] where he scored his debut for Bohs on 3 January 1994 in a 2-0 league win over [[Cobh Ramblers]].<ref>Bohemian FC match programme, Vol. 46, no. 5</ref> He made 4 appearances in European competition for Bohs, all of them in the 1995 [[Intertoto Cup]].\n\nCooney earned caps for the [[Republic of Ireland national under-19 football team|Republic of Ireland national under-19 team]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cooney, Wayne}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland association footballers]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n[[Category:Shamrock Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bohemian F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Dundalk F.C. players]]\n[[Category:League of Ireland players]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:English people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Birmingham, West Midlands]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayne_Cooney"}
