e\u00e1 |year=1979 |orig-year=1937 |title=Red Spanish Notebook |publisher = City Lights Books (originally by Martin Secker & Warburg) |location=San Francisco |isbn = 0-87286-132-5 |oclc=4832126}}\n* {{cite book |last=Monteath |first=Peter |year= 1994 |title= The Spanish Civil War in literature, film, and art: an international Bibliography of secondary literature |publisher=Greenwood Press |location=Westport, CT |isbn = 0-313-29262-0}}\n* P\u00e9rez de Urbel, Justo (1993). ''Catholic Martyrs of the Spanish Civil War, 1936\u20131939'', trans. by Michael F. Ingrams. Kansas City, MO: Angelus Press. {{ISBN|0-935952-96-9}}\n* {{cite book |last=Preston |first=Paul |orig-year=2012 |year = 2012 |title=The Spanish Holocaust: Inquisition and Extermination in Twentieth-Century Spain |publisher =Harper Press |location=London |isbn=978-0-00-255634-7}}\n* {{cite book |last=Puzzo |first=Dante Anthony |year=1962 |title=Spain and the Great Powers, 1936\u20131941 |publisher = Books for Libraries Press (originally Columbia University Press, N.Y.) |location= Freeport, NY |isbn = 0-8369-6868-9 |oclc = 308726}}\n* {{cite book |last=Southworth |first=Herbert Rutledge |year= 1963 |language = es |title= El mito de la cruzada de Franco |trans-title=The Myth of Franco's crusade |publisher=Ruedo Ib\u00e9rico |location= Paris |isbn = 84-8346-574-4}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Wheeler |first1=George |first2=Jack |last2 = Jones |author2-link=Jack Jones (trade unionist) |editor-first = David |editor-last = Leach |year=2003 |title = To Make the People Smile Again: a Memoir of the Spanish Civil War |publisher=Zymurgy Publishing |location=Newcastle upon Tyne |isbn = 1-903506-07-7 |oclc = 231998540}} (trade unionist)\n* {{cite book |last=Wilson |first=Ann |year=1986 |title = Images of the Civil War |publisher=Allen & Unwin |location = London}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n\n=== Films, images and sounds ===\n; Films\n* [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL4w-2j6Q0Qj4iJ7GmEoQGWMUBeE