 de las Juntas de Ofensiva Nacional Sindicalista|FET y de las JONS]]{{efn|The only party under [[Francisco Franco]] from 1937 onward, a [[Unification Decree (Spain, 1937)|merger of the other factions on the Nationalist side]].|name=\"FetJons\"}}}}\n* {{nowrap|{{Flagicon image|Bandera FE JONS.svg}} [[Falange Espa\u00f1ola de las JONS|FE de las JONS]]{{efn|1936\u20131937, then merged into [[Falange Espa\u00f1ola Tradicionalista y de las Juntas de Ofensiva Nacional Sindicalista|FET y de las JONS]]|name=\"Natmerge\"}}}}\n* {{flagicon image|Flag of Traditionalist Requetes.svg}} [[Requet\u00e9s]]/[[Traditionalist Communion|CT]]{{efn|1936\u20131937, then merged into [[Falange Espa\u00f1ola Tradicionalista y de las Juntas de Ofensiva Nacional Sindicalista|FET y de las JONS]]|name=\"Natmerge\"}}\n* {{flagicon image|CEDA flag.svg}} [[Spanish Confederation of Autonomous Right-wing Groups|CEDA]]{{efn|1936\u20131937, then merged into [[Falange Espa\u00f1ola Tradicionalista y de las Juntas de Ofensiva Nacional Sindicalista|FET y de las JONS]]|name=\"Natmerge\"}}\n* {{nowrap|{{flagicon image|Bandera de Renovaci\u00f3n Espa\u00f1ola.svg}} [[Renovaci\u00f3n Espa\u00f1ola]]{{efn|1936\u20131937, then merged into [[Falange Espa\u00f1ola Tradicionalista y de las Juntas de Ofensiva Nacional Sindicalista|FET y de las JONS]]|name=\"Natmerge\"}}}}\n* {{flagicon image|Merchant flag of Spanish Morocco.svg}} [[Army of Africa (Spain)|Army of Africa]]\n{{plainlist|\n* {{flagicon|Kingdom of Italy}} [[Italian military intervention in Spain|Italy]]\n* {{flagicon|Nazi Germany}} [[German involvement in the Spanish Civil War|Germany]]\n* '''Supported by:'''\n* {{flagdeco|Portugal}} [[Estado Novo (Portugal)|Portugal]]\n* {{flagicon|Holy See}} [[Holy See]] <small>(diplomatic)</small>\n* [[foreign involvement in the Spanish Civil War#Nationalist foreign volunteers|Foreign volunteers]]\n}}\n| commander1  = {{plainlist|\n* {{flagicon|Spanish Republic}}{{flagicon image|Flag of the Popular Front (Spain).svg}